text.section:
An angler's license is not required of the following:
The owner or tenant of land bordering on nontidal water, his spouse and children, or the spouse of any child who resides on the land with the owner or tenant when he fishes in nontidal water adjoining his land;
Any resident serving in the armed forces of the United States, while on leave in the State, during his leave period, if, while angling, he possesses a copy of his official leave orders;
A person who fishes in nontidal waters of the State on free fishing days designated by the Secretary;
A person holding a current resident consolidated senior sport fishing license issued under § 4-216 of this title;
A person fishing in a free fishing area established under § 4-214(b)(2) of this title; or
A person authorized by a disability exemption issued under § 4-217 of this title.
